description:
&lt;p&gt;Whether you are a newly qualified nurse or experience we would love you to come and join the brilliant Intensive Care Unit Critical at Epsom and St Helier University NHS Hospitals&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Imagine working as a band 5 staff nurse within a friendly within a forward thinking and dynamic intensive care unit. The intensive care team is committed to ‘making every busy day a good day ‘ our patients and their families tell us that we provide compassionate , kind care and that our staff have happy faces with big smiles . We believe that this is because we respect and care for one another due to all our staff feeling valued at work. Making sure you are happy and fulfilled at work is our top priority as we know happy staff means wonderful patient care is delivered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The intensive care footprint is across two sites based at St Helier and Epsom Hospital. The case mix is diverse and will definitely keep you busy and on your critical care toes!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our benefits package is substantial and includes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Newly qualified preceptor programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Introduction to critical care course&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rotation programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working and help finding accommodation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flu vaccinations and staff wellbeing service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Next Steps &lt;/strong&gt;- please complete an application form and we will be in touch !&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Julia Arkell  Lead Nurse for Recruitment and Retention&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email addressJulia.Arkell@nhs.net   Telephone number 07500101088&lt;/p&gt;
